  "texts": [
    "First, FELLAS does not introduce significant communication overhead, as the basic training flow of FedSeqRec remains unchanged.",
    "Additionally, computational costs are not substantially increased, since clients continue training with traditional sequential recommender systems, which are much more lightweight than LLM-based models.",
    "Finally, FELLAS maintains the inference speed of traditional sequential recommendation models while leveraging the powerful representational abilities of LLMs.",
    "As a result, FELLAS offers a more practical approach.",
    "Figure 2 presents the details of our FELLAS architecture."
